comments: Murray (DEN) makes foot to foot contact with Gilgeous-Alexander (OKC) that dislodges him from his position during the drive.
Gordon (DEN) is in the paint for at or about three seconds when he moves to imminently guard an opponent.
Giddey (OKC) is in the paint for less than three seconds when he moves to imminently guard Gordon (DEN).
Giddey (OKC) gets to the height of the ball and makes contact with the ball and with Gordon's (DEN) hand that is attached to the ball while defending the shot attempt.
Gilgeous-Alexander (OKC) establishes his right foot as his pivot and maintains it prior to releasing the pass.
Murray (DEN) moves alongside Giddey's (OKC) path and marginal body contact occurs during the driving shot attempt.
Gilgeous-Alexander (OKC) makes contact with Brown's (DEN) left arm, which causes him to lose the ball OOB during the driving shot attempt.
Brown (DEN) is the last player to touch the ball before it goes OOB.
Gilgeous-Alexander (OKC) follows-through on Murray's (DEN) left arm after making some contact with the ball and affects his driving shot attempt.
Williams (OKC) initiates contact with Nnaji's (DEN) left arm, which affects his play at the basket.
Giddey (OKC) releases the in-bounds pass within 5 seconds.
Following the whistled foul on Williams (OKC), the game clock continues to run. The game clock is then correctly reset.
Caldwell-Pope (DEN) extends his left leg out and makes intentional foot to ball contact.
Nanji (DEN) is in the paint for less than three seconds when he moves to imminently guard Williams (OKC). Nanji then exits the lane in less than three seconds.
Brown (DEN) is actively guarding Williams (OKC) before Williams moves away. Brown is then in the paint for less than three seconds when he moves to imminently guard Williams.
Giddey (OKC) releases the in-bounds pass within 5 seconds.
Gordon (DEN) slides a slight hand across and off Gilgeous-Alexander's (OKC) front and marginal contact occurs during the shot attempt near the basket.
Gilgeous-Alexander (OKC) is in the paint for at or about three seconds when he moves to imminently guard an opponent.
Dort (OKC) contests the jump shot attempt and avoids making contact with Murray's (DEN) arms.
